for someone dedicating their life to being The Most Tortured man, kiefer comes across as fundamentally untortured

Movie: Cairo as Told by Youssef Chahine

Review: computerized catholic aesthetics before they were made unbearable by substack writers and shitposters, insane soundtrack (i would also like to see this only set to drum and bass), a yo la tengo cameo, a shoutout to papples (the pear-apple crossbreeds that nobody has ever believed me exist), and pj harvey is hot af!!!
this is what a woman is? this is what a woman is in the dark and twisted mind of zach braff? disgusting!
yes the modern love scene can stand alone as one of the greatest of all time but there was a lot more to enjoy!
